      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantities of interest used in validation must be shown to be relevant to the clinical decision at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and modified index of hemolysis (MIH) were identified as primary quantities of interest. Their direct relevance to blood trauma assessment in CPB devices is established in peer-reviewed literature and FDA guidance documents."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
